WEBVTT

00:38.872 --> 00:40.457
(door creaks)

00:45.045 --> 00:46.254
(sighs)

00:59.851 --> 01:01.394
(phone beeping)

01:02.103 --> 01:04.356
(line ringing)

01:05.357 --> 01:06.399
Charlie: (over phone)
Yeah?

01:06.441 --> 01:07.734
Charlie.

01:08.943 --> 01:10.362
Long time no time.

01:13.281 --> 01:15.241
You know who this is?

01:15.283 --> 01:18.536
Charlie: Mr. Sterling.
Yeah, it's, uh, been a while.

01:18.578 --> 01:19.704
My God, kid.

01:21.623 --> 01:22.707
It's a mess, isn't it?

01:27.962 --> 01:29.839
Just spoke to
the medical examiner.

01:32.133 --> 01:34.260
There wasn't enough
of my son

01:34.302 --> 01:36.137
for me to even identify.

01:38.181 --> 01:39.641
It's a fucking mess, kid.

01:45.563 --> 01:47.607
I let you off once,
Charlie.

01:47.649 --> 01:48.775
Gave you a life.

01:50.068 --> 01:51.528
Pretty good life, right?

01:53.154 --> 01:56.157
Charlie:
So, uh, what happens now?

01:58.493 --> 02:00.161
You tell me where you are.

02:01.454 --> 02:05.625
I mean, you might as well
tell me where you are.

02:05.667 --> 02:08.128
'Cause there's is not
a corner in this country

02:08.169 --> 02:09.796
small enough
for you to hide in.

02:11.297 --> 02:13.299
There's no off the grid

02:13.341 --> 02:16.720
that's off-the-grid enough
for you to hide from me.

02:16.761 --> 02:19.139
I'm a tough old bastard
and I got some years left.

02:19.180 --> 02:20.265
(door opens)

02:20.306 --> 02:22.183
And I'm gonna
spend them finding you.

02:23.685 --> 02:25.687
And I'm going to hit you
where it hurts.

02:26.980 --> 02:29.274
And when I
do kill you, finally...

02:31.693 --> 02:33.194
you can thank me.

02:34.571 --> 02:35.613
Now...

02:36.781 --> 02:37.907
tell me, kid...

02:40.785 --> 02:42.287
am I lyin'?

02:44.330 --> 02:45.665
Charlie:
I got to go.

02:46.958 --> 02:48.335
(line disconnects)

02:51.713 --> 02:54.049
This is your job now.

02:54.090 --> 02:56.051
You're going to find
Charlie Cale,

02:56.092 --> 02:57.886
and then
you're gonna call me

02:59.220 --> 03:01.264
and you're gonna ask me

03:01.306 --> 03:03.475
how deep to dig the hole.

03:15.653 --> 03:18.114
Cliff:
Well, that was quick.

03:18.156 --> 03:20.158
ATM ping off highway 93.

03:20.200 --> 03:21.534
On my way.

03:22.077 --> 03:23.286
We got her.

03:23.328 --> 03:24.746
I found her.

03:24.788 --> 03:27.040
Yeah, she's headed west.

03:27.082 --> 03:28.291
LA.

03:29.793 --> 03:31.211
(whimsical jazz playing)

03:31.252 --> 03:33.797
Wait, wait, wait.
What do you mean "Texas"?

03:35.215 --> 03:36.508
Yes. I asked him.

03:36.549 --> 03:38.218
Don't you think
I asked him that?

03:38.259 --> 03:39.594
Sterling Sr.: (over phone)
Goddammit.

03:43.765 --> 03:44.766
(phone buzzing)

03:51.231 --> 03:54.609
* *

03:55.985 --> 03:57.612
Yeah, a week ago.

03:57.654 --> 04:00.281
-No, she's gone.
-Sterling Sr.: Dammit.

04:01.491 --> 04:03.243
Well, that's a good question.

04:03.284 --> 04:04.744
Allow me
to introduce myself.

04:04.786 --> 04:06.454
-My name is...
-(explosion booms)

04:06.496 --> 04:08.373
Man: (on TV)
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

04:08.415 --> 04:10.083
Michael: (on TV) And I'm
from the department of...

04:10.125 --> 04:11.209
(explosion booms)

04:11.251 --> 04:12.585
Cliff:
A year.

04:13.378 --> 04:15.213
Over a year.

04:15.255 --> 04:17.340
Over a year
of shitty coffee

04:17.382 --> 04:18.508
and bad motels.

04:18.550 --> 04:20.468
The things
that I have eaten.

04:21.636 --> 04:24.556
A solid year on the road.

04:24.597 --> 04:26.266
I did not sign up for this.

04:26.307 --> 04:28.268
I should be there with you
running our business,

04:28.309 --> 04:29.686
doing my job.

04:29.728 --> 04:32.063
Not out here chasing
some delinquent runaway.

04:32.105 --> 04:34.107
Sterling Sr.: (over phone)
I thought
I made it clear to you.

04:34.149 --> 04:35.859
This is your job.

04:35.900 --> 04:37.402
And all you're telling me
right now

04:37.444 --> 04:39.779
is that you're bad
at your job.

04:39.821 --> 04:41.698
Not sure why you'd
even go out of your way

04:41.740 --> 04:44.034
to point that out
to your employer.

04:44.075 --> 04:45.035
Call you back.

04:46.911 --> 04:48.163
Yeah. Parker.

04:48.204 --> 04:50.623
Parker:
Hey, we got something
in Colorado.

04:50.665 --> 04:52.042
Your troubles may be over.

04:56.254 --> 04:57.839
(music ends)

04:59.632 --> 05:01.593
Let me take a look
at that Jane Doe.

05:03.636 --> 05:05.889
It's over. We got her.

05:05.930 --> 05:09.809
All I need to know is
how deep to dig the hole.

05:09.851 --> 05:12.937
Sterling Sr.:
We're gonna
let her heal up.

05:12.979 --> 05:15.690
Cliff: Well, that,
that might take some time.

05:15.732 --> 05:17.692
Like, like multiple months.

05:17.734 --> 05:20.028
She's conscious,
just incapacitated.

05:20.070 --> 05:21.571
I can make it hurt
right now.

05:21.613 --> 05:23.323
Sterling Sr.:
No. Two months is fine.

05:23.365 --> 05:24.866
I can wait.

05:24.908 --> 05:26.326
I want her on her feet.

05:26.368 --> 05:28.328
Then you're gonna
bring her to me.

05:28.370 --> 05:30.455
You camp out
outside that hospital

05:30.497 --> 05:31.831
until she's discharged.

05:31.873 --> 05:33.416
And don't let her
slip past you again.

05:33.458 --> 05:35.543
Are you,
are you fucking kidding me?

05:35.585 --> 05:37.587
If you think I'm sitting
at some shit motel

05:37.629 --> 05:38.755
in fucking Denver--

05:40.340 --> 05:41.841
Michael: (on TV)
Jimmy, what are you doing?

05:41.883 --> 05:44.260
Motherfucker.

05:44.302 --> 05:45.303
Now the people
who did this are putting

05:45.345 --> 05:46.596
the screws to me too.

05:46.638 --> 05:48.765
I don't wanna be here
any more than you do.

05:48.807 --> 05:50.975
If you can be good,
you get to ride up front.

05:54.437 --> 05:58.692
(indistinct announcement
over PA)

05:58.733 --> 06:00.485
Jacob!

06:00.527 --> 06:02.487
You take care
of yourself, man, alright?

06:02.529 --> 06:04.447
Thanks.
Good luck.

06:05.448 --> 06:07.826
Janelle, I'm going
to miss you, lady.

06:07.867 --> 06:10.495
-Bye, sweetheart.
-Bye, honey. Thanks.

06:10.537 --> 06:12.539
Edwin, It's been real,

06:12.580 --> 06:15.458
but I'm afraid
it's checkout time.

06:15.500 --> 06:17.669
I'm going to give you guys
five stars on Yelp,

06:17.711 --> 06:19.212
no doubt.

06:19.254 --> 06:22.382
So, uh, bill-wise,

06:22.424 --> 06:23.967
I'm not sure
how this works.

06:24.009 --> 06:26.678
If you have an installment plan
or something.

06:26.720 --> 06:29.055
Uh, your bill's been paid
since day one.

06:30.056 --> 06:31.474
My God.

06:31.516 --> 06:33.268
Thanks, Obama.

06:33.309 --> 06:35.729
What? No.
By private party.

06:35.770 --> 06:37.647
You've been here
two months.

06:37.689 --> 06:40.066
You had a room
with a TV.

06:40.108 --> 06:41.860
How do you think this works?

06:41.901 --> 06:44.821
I don't know, I guess I thought
you guys were like a, a church

06:44.863 --> 06:46.740
you know,
can't turn people away.

06:46.781 --> 06:48.575
Ha, ha.

06:48.616 --> 06:53.288
Wait, a... private party.

06:53.329 --> 06:55.582
(Sammy Turner's
"Lavender Blue" playing)

07:01.171 --> 07:07.135
* Lavender blue *

07:07.177 --> 07:10.096
* Dilly-dilly *

07:10.138 --> 07:12.098
* Lavender... *

07:12.140 --> 07:13.975
Trunk or the cab?

07:14.017 --> 07:15.393
Either way works for me.

07:15.435 --> 07:20.106
* If I were king *

07:20.148 --> 07:22.233
* Dilly-dilly *

07:22.275 --> 07:23.735
(thumping)

07:23.777 --> 07:25.445
Charlie:
Hey! Okay.

07:25.487 --> 07:27.739
* *

07:30.492 --> 07:32.077
Well...

07:32.118 --> 07:35.538
* Dilly-dilly *

07:35.580 --> 07:41.127
* You'll be my queen *

07:41.169 --> 07:43.254
* Lavender blue *

07:43.296 --> 07:45.507
Man: (on TV)
Drop it and show me
your hands.

07:45.548 --> 07:49.010
* Dilly-dilly *

07:50.345 --> 07:51.721
You think he's going
to make it hurt?

07:53.014 --> 07:54.015
One can hope.

07:54.974 --> 07:56.476
Yeah.

07:56.518 --> 07:58.770
It's a relief
in a sick way.

07:58.812 --> 08:00.980
I can feel the muscles
in my brain relaxing

08:01.022 --> 08:02.857
that haven't been relaxed
in a year.

08:03.858 --> 08:07.487
All this,
everywhere I went,

08:07.529 --> 08:09.572
it felt like
I was leasing time.

08:10.365 --> 08:12.325
Yeah.

08:12.367 --> 08:14.119
I know he'd
get me eventually.

08:15.912 --> 08:16.955
Inevitable.

08:18.123 --> 08:19.541
The hook.

08:20.417 --> 08:22.335
-Eh?
-The hook.

08:22.377 --> 08:25.130
Brings you back.
Inevitable.

08:25.171 --> 08:27.048
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

08:30.719 --> 08:31.970
You killed Natalie, right?

08:32.012 --> 08:34.556
Like, Sterling Jr.
gave the word, but...

08:35.390 --> 08:36.808
you killed her, right?

08:51.406 --> 08:53.074
Open the glove compartment.

09:06.421 --> 09:07.756
Reach in
and take it out.

10:06.064 --> 10:07.357
(gun clatters)

10:13.029 --> 10:15.073
(engine revving)

10:15.115 --> 10:16.908
(bird cawing)

10:22.330 --> 10:23.873
Suck it in.

10:23.915 --> 10:26.626
Suck it in,
suck it in.

10:26.668 --> 10:29.838
If you're Rin Tin Tin
or Anne Boleyn.

10:29.879 --> 10:32.841
Make a desperate move
or else he'll win.

10:33.842 --> 10:35.802
And then begin to see

10:35.844 --> 10:37.470
what you're doing to me.

10:37.512 --> 10:39.681
This MTV is not for free.

10:39.723 --> 10:41.266
It's so PC
it's killing me.

10:41.307 --> 10:43.643
So, desperately,
I'll sing to thee of love.

10:43.685 --> 10:46.438
Sure, but also rage
and hate and pain

10:46.479 --> 10:48.106
and fear of self.

10:48.148 --> 10:50.108
And I can't keep
these feelings to myself.

10:50.150 --> 10:52.652
I've tried.
Well, no, in fact, I lied.

10:52.694 --> 10:54.821
Could be financial suicide

10:54.863 --> 10:56.406
but I've got
too much pride inside

10:56.448 --> 10:58.408
to hide or slide.

10:58.450 --> 11:00.869
I'll do as I'll decide
and let it ride until I've died.

11:00.910 --> 11:02.495
And only then shall I
abide this tide

11:02.537 --> 11:05.498
of catchy little tunes.

11:05.540 --> 11:07.042
Of hip
three-minute ditties.

11:07.083 --> 11:08.460
I want to bust
all your balloons.

11:08.501 --> 11:10.837
I want to burn all of
your cities to the ground.

11:10.879 --> 11:13.173
I've found I will not mess
around unless I play.

11:13.214 --> 11:15.383
Then, hey,
I will go on all day.

11:15.425 --> 11:16.968
Hear what I say.

11:17.010 --> 11:18.678
I have a prayer
to pray.

11:18.720 --> 11:20.764
That's really
all this was.

11:20.805 --> 11:22.932
When I'm feeling stuck
and need a buck,

11:22.974 --> 11:24.559
I don't rely on luck.

11:24.601 --> 11:26.644
Because the hook

11:26.686 --> 11:29.105
brings you back.

11:31.566 --> 11:33.777
You really are
the fucking worst.

11:41.868 --> 11:46.748
(bright big band music plays)

11:46.790 --> 11:48.333
Hey, w-w-what is this?

11:48.375 --> 11:50.418
Like, when Pesci gets
whacked in "Goodfellas"?

11:50.460 --> 11:53.171
Is that the, uh,
just keep walking?

11:53.213 --> 11:54.422
(lock clicks)

11:57.550 --> 11:58.635
Fuck, man.

12:01.054 --> 12:03.056
Get cleaned up.
Put that on.

12:03.098 --> 12:04.432
I'll be back in an hour.

12:07.727 --> 12:09.270
(door closes)

12:14.693 --> 12:15.985
Okay. Alright.

12:24.786 --> 12:26.996
(slot machines chiming)

12:36.589 --> 12:39.592
* *

12:46.808 --> 12:47.767
Hey, kid.

12:54.399 --> 12:55.692
Want a drink?

12:56.776 --> 12:58.486
No. Uh...

13:02.824 --> 13:03.825
Yeah.

13:04.617 --> 13:05.577
A beer.

13:10.707 --> 13:11.916
(scoffs)

13:15.795 --> 13:17.464
Charlie: Alright.

13:17.505 --> 13:19.466
You got me.
What happens?

13:22.135 --> 13:23.720
Tell me about your year.

13:24.637 --> 13:25.889
No. No.

13:25.930 --> 13:27.932
My year's been a knot
in my stomach every night,

13:27.974 --> 13:29.225
knowing this was coming.

13:29.267 --> 13:31.519
So now it's here.
Just do me the dignity.

13:31.561 --> 13:33.021
You won.
Just do me the dignity

13:33.063 --> 13:34.814
of skipping this
cat-and-mouse shit

13:34.856 --> 13:36.608
and whatever
you're gonna do, just do it.

13:38.234 --> 13:39.819
What did you think
was gonna happen?

13:41.654 --> 13:44.115
Now, I just want
to talk, huh?

13:44.157 --> 13:46.701
Hey, take the win, kid.

13:48.745 --> 13:49.788
Thanks.

13:51.247 --> 13:53.249
You grew up
in Atlantic City, right?

13:53.291 --> 13:54.876
You got family here,
right?

13:57.170 --> 13:59.464
Hey, I didn't mean that
to be threatening.

13:59.506 --> 14:01.383
I just, you know,

14:01.424 --> 14:03.510
I know so little about you,
I heard that,

14:03.551 --> 14:05.345
I thought
it was interesting.

14:05.387 --> 14:07.305
Yeah.

14:07.347 --> 14:08.890
Fuck it. Doesn't matter.

14:10.183 --> 14:12.477
This casino is owned

14:12.519 --> 14:15.105
by the Hasp family.

14:15.146 --> 14:18.483
Beatrix Hasp,
real piece of work.

14:18.525 --> 14:20.985
Not very nice people.

14:21.027 --> 14:23.405
You can feel it
comin' up from the floor.

14:23.446 --> 14:25.949
I can, sittin' at the tables,
I can feel it.

14:27.701 --> 14:29.035
It's funny

14:29.077 --> 14:31.663
how it seeps all the way
down through the bedrock.

14:33.957 --> 14:35.125
(sighs)

14:35.166 --> 14:36.376
And even still...

14:38.086 --> 14:41.131
there's no place
I would rather be
than a casino floor.

14:42.590 --> 14:44.718
I tried retiring.

14:44.759 --> 14:45.969
I tried golf.

14:47.846 --> 14:50.015
It's fine.

14:50.056 --> 14:52.726
I just kept getting
pulled back, you know.

14:53.727 --> 14:55.437
There's nothing
that pulls you in more

14:55.478 --> 14:56.855
than being really good

14:56.896 --> 14:59.149
at something
for unhealthy reasons.

15:00.066 --> 15:01.651
Running a casino,

15:02.694 --> 15:04.529
that's what does it for me.

15:04.571 --> 15:07.032
I'm very good at it.

15:07.073 --> 15:10.201
For the exact same reasons
I'm lousy at being a father.

15:10.243 --> 15:11.161
How about that?

15:12.620 --> 15:14.581
Any of this making
any sense to you?

15:16.082 --> 15:17.459
I didn't kill your son.

15:18.168 --> 15:19.419
And I want you to know

15:19.461 --> 15:21.546
what he did

15:21.588 --> 15:24.049
and what Kazimir Caine did

15:24.090 --> 15:25.383
and why I did what I--

15:25.425 --> 15:27.385
-I know.
-You know?

15:27.427 --> 15:29.095
I know.

15:29.137 --> 15:30.180
And I understand.

15:30.221 --> 15:31.806
I would have done
the same thing.

15:31.848 --> 15:34.351
I don't blame you
for my son's death.

15:34.392 --> 15:35.518
Well, what?

15:35.560 --> 15:36.936
Sterling, what the fuck

15:36.978 --> 15:38.480
have we been doing
for this past year?

15:38.521 --> 15:40.231
-I've been chasing you.
-Why?

15:40.273 --> 15:41.441
Because you've been runnin'.

15:41.483 --> 15:42.901
I was running
because you were chasing me.

15:42.942 --> 15:45.236
What the fuck
is even happening right now?

15:45.278 --> 15:46.613
And now I caught you.

15:46.654 --> 15:48.198
Yes.

15:48.239 --> 15:51.117
And now... what?

15:54.913 --> 15:57.999
If I stood up
and walked away right now,

15:58.041 --> 15:59.167
so what happens?

16:00.001 --> 16:01.419
Go ahead.

16:01.461 --> 16:03.254
Your car's cleaned up
and serviced.

16:03.296 --> 16:06.633
Hey, it's in
the west valet. Here.

16:07.801 --> 16:09.219
I don't think
you will though.

16:10.136 --> 16:11.763
I'm not gonna hurt you.

16:11.805 --> 16:14.099
And you know
I'm not lying.

16:14.140 --> 16:15.308
But I think you're curious

16:15.350 --> 16:17.143
why I got you here.

16:37.539 --> 16:38.498
(Charlie sighs)

16:38.540 --> 16:40.208
I know
I had you hooked.

16:45.255 --> 16:47.215
Sterling Jr.:
Can you do your thing
over video?

16:47.257 --> 16:48.466
Charlie:
Yeah, I think so.

16:48.508 --> 16:49.592
And so when is this game?

16:49.634 --> 16:51.052
Sterling Jr.:
Day after tomorrow.

16:51.094 --> 16:52.220
We got 48 hours.

16:52.262 --> 16:54.431
Charlie: Uh, and,
and your dad's alright

16:54.472 --> 16:57.225
with this, uh,
us plucking his golden goose?

16:57.267 --> 16:58.768
Sterling Jr.:
My dad?

17:00.520 --> 17:02.814
You recognize that?

17:02.856 --> 17:04.649
I've had the whole place
tapped for sound

17:04.691 --> 17:06.067
since the early '80s.

17:06.109 --> 17:07.569
Yeah, evidently.

17:07.610 --> 17:09.571
In tape I trust.

17:09.612 --> 17:11.656
-(tape rewinding)
-But there's this.

17:11.698 --> 17:13.366
This happened
right before

17:13.408 --> 17:14.951
your meeting
with my son.

17:16.036 --> 17:19.164
He's in his office
all by himself. Right?

17:19.205 --> 17:20.915
His private line rings.

17:22.917 --> 17:24.669
(phone rings)

17:24.711 --> 17:26.546
Sterling Jr.:
Not here.

17:27.964 --> 17:30.300
-"Not here."
-Sterling Sr.: "Not here."

17:30.342 --> 17:32.093
Meaning,
don't call me here.

17:32.135 --> 17:33.887
Because he knew
I could trace the number,

17:33.928 --> 17:35.680
which I did.

17:35.722 --> 17:38.016
It came from the owner
of this casino,

17:38.058 --> 17:39.642
Beatrix Hasp.

17:39.684 --> 17:41.353
There's three things
I said to my kid

17:41.394 --> 17:43.313
before I gave him
the keys to the casino.

17:43.355 --> 17:45.440
First two don't matter.

17:45.482 --> 17:46.691
The third one...

17:48.068 --> 17:49.944
keep Beatrix Hasp out.

17:49.986 --> 17:51.863
She's the head
of the Five Families,

17:51.905 --> 17:54.032
which is exactly
what it sounds like.

17:54.074 --> 17:57.077
They've wanted a piece
of Frost Nevada forever.

17:57.118 --> 17:58.912
I keep 'em out.

17:58.953 --> 18:00.747
They're not happy
about this.

18:01.581 --> 18:02.791
My son...

18:04.000 --> 18:05.794
he was making
a deal with Beatrix

18:05.835 --> 18:07.253
and the Five Families

18:07.295 --> 18:08.963
behind my back.

18:09.923 --> 18:11.049
Okay.

18:11.091 --> 18:12.050
Sterling Sr.:
Today, there's a sit-down

18:12.092 --> 18:14.719
between me
and the Five Families.

18:14.761 --> 18:18.264
That's why I'm here.
At her hotel.

18:18.306 --> 18:21.059
Cliff didn't like the idea
of doing it on her turf.

