34:55.970 --> 34:57.180
"that's your Auntie Charlie,

34:57.222 --> 35:00.016
who you met once
when you were three."

35:00.058 --> 35:02.435
It's great to see you.
Just great.

35:02.477 --> 35:06.773
Jesus. Look, Em, do you have
any olive oil or something?

35:06.815 --> 35:08.983
-What?
-I just need it for just...

35:10.694 --> 35:12.987
Weird.
Uh, never mind.

35:13.029 --> 35:15.115
You know, I ought a march you
out to the cops right now?

35:15.156 --> 35:16.741
-Don't, please. Don't, please.
-Yeah. Yeah.

35:16.783 --> 35:18.451
I'll regret it the rest
of my life if I don't.

35:18.493 --> 35:20.286
Look, I, I, you know
I don't want to come
here like this. Okay.

35:20.328 --> 35:22.539
The last thing in the world
I want to do is
come to you like this.

35:22.580 --> 35:24.833
Alright? You know that. Alright?
So just, I just need one thing.

35:24.874 --> 35:27.544
-Oh, you need one thing. God!
-I need one thing!

35:27.585 --> 35:29.045
One thing,
and then I'll go.

35:29.087 --> 35:31.006
-Why do I always get
pulled into shit with you?
-Dude.

35:31.047 --> 35:34.217
Saving you when
you're just ruinous.

35:35.802 --> 35:37.929
You are ruinous.

35:45.854 --> 35:49.232
Jesus. Em. Em.

35:49.274 --> 35:51.818
-Just--
-Would you keep it down,
please. She's...

35:51.860 --> 35:53.611
I'm sorry.

35:53.653 --> 35:56.865
Look, I want to know, uh...

35:57.657 --> 35:58.908
did you, uh...

35:59.868 --> 36:01.494
I sent you...

36:01.536 --> 36:04.164
A couple of years back,
I, uh, sent you, uh...

36:04.205 --> 36:05.206
The money?

36:06.708 --> 36:08.043
So what do you want now?

36:08.084 --> 36:10.545
Me to thank you
for the money?

36:10.587 --> 36:12.505
-I--
-Or that's what you need?

36:12.547 --> 36:13.757
You need money?

36:13.798 --> 36:15.467
No, no.
(stammers)

36:15.508 --> 36:17.510
Look, I just wanted,
I didn't know if you got it.

36:17.552 --> 36:18.887
I just wanted to know

36:19.554 --> 36:20.555
that you did...

36:21.681 --> 36:22.891
get it.

36:27.062 --> 36:28.646
Alright, look, I, uh,

36:29.898 --> 36:31.399
I can be gone
in two minutes.

36:33.568 --> 36:35.403
I just,
I need Dad's boat.

36:35.445 --> 36:36.905
(scoffs)

36:45.330 --> 36:48.500
(clattering)

36:48.541 --> 36:49.584
Em.

36:50.919 --> 36:52.879
Thanks.
Thank you.

36:52.921 --> 36:54.255
You're fuckin' welcome.

36:55.382 --> 36:56.841
Jesus.

36:56.883 --> 36:58.259
I'll wait over there.

37:01.721 --> 37:06.184
(TV playing, indistinct)

37:08.895 --> 37:09.979
Hello.

37:10.605 --> 37:12.273
Hello.

37:12.315 --> 37:16.069
I'm Charlie. I'm, uh,
I'm your mom's sister.

37:16.111 --> 37:18.738
So that makes me
your aunt.

37:18.780 --> 37:20.532
You swim?

37:20.573 --> 37:21.449
Do I swim?

37:22.909 --> 37:25.245
I haven't swam in years.

37:25.286 --> 37:26.955
Why? Do I look
like I swim?

37:28.289 --> 37:29.249
I, uh...

37:30.333 --> 37:31.459
Okay.

37:34.462 --> 37:36.589
And who didn't believe
I could do it?

37:37.799 --> 37:38.717
Who doubted me?

37:43.346 --> 37:44.556
Well, hello.

37:45.348 --> 37:46.307
That's, uh...

37:47.684 --> 37:49.436
yeah, that's me
and your mom.

37:49.477 --> 37:51.146
(scoffs) Yeah.

37:51.187 --> 37:55.275
Well, uh, Dad,
I'm sorry,

37:55.316 --> 37:58.403
Granddad used to take us
out on his boat,

37:58.445 --> 38:02.532
and then he'd make us
swim back to shore, so...

38:03.575 --> 38:04.826
That was fun.

38:04.868 --> 38:06.369
I like swimming.

38:06.411 --> 38:08.038
Charlie:
Ah, you do?
That's good.

38:08.079 --> 38:09.956
Yeah, I hate it.

38:09.998 --> 38:12.250
Then why'd you do it?

38:12.292 --> 38:16.796
Well, I guess I was good
at it for some reason and...

38:16.838 --> 38:18.465
You know, you end up
in the water,

38:18.506 --> 38:20.258
what else are you going
to do? Right?

38:22.093 --> 38:24.137
Emily:
Shasta.

38:24.179 --> 38:26.806
Auntie Charlie
was just saying goodbye.

38:26.848 --> 38:28.224
You say goodbye to her?

38:29.893 --> 38:31.102
Goodbye.

38:31.644 --> 38:32.687
Bye-bye.

38:32.729 --> 38:35.607
Baby, what is that
in, in Jan's hair?

38:35.648 --> 38:38.818
It's a hot roller.
I'm giving her a perm.

38:38.860 --> 38:40.403
Aunt Charlie dropped it.

38:46.409 --> 38:48.828
Okay. I'm sorry
about that.

38:48.870 --> 38:50.455
It's my hair-do. It's...

38:50.497 --> 38:52.123
Yeah, okay.

38:52.165 --> 38:54.167
Shasta seems
like a good kid.

38:55.251 --> 38:58.380
I'm sorry I didn't
ever get to, uh...

38:58.421 --> 39:00.965
Well, I have a situation
I have to get out of.

39:01.007 --> 39:04.052
But after that,
if you'd allow it,

39:04.094 --> 39:06.429
you know,
I'd love to try to...

39:08.139 --> 39:09.683
I mean, we should talk
at least, right?

39:13.395 --> 39:14.396
No.

39:16.898 --> 39:18.066
No.

39:18.108 --> 39:20.777
I mean, there's a world
where we get to talk.

39:21.778 --> 39:25.031
We, we hash out
the past,

39:25.073 --> 39:26.241
talk about Dad,

39:27.200 --> 39:28.326
what you did,

39:28.993 --> 39:31.037
what you ruined

39:31.079 --> 39:33.164
with your truth
and bullshit.

39:34.374 --> 39:35.959
You learn more
about my life,

39:36.001 --> 39:38.712
my kid,
and we build that.

39:42.590 --> 39:45.802
But that's not
the life you chose.

39:45.844 --> 39:47.554
That's not
"The Charlie Show."

39:48.596 --> 39:53.059
You think I chose this,
like, doing this?

39:53.101 --> 39:54.853
You think I like
living like this?

39:54.894 --> 39:56.062
I don't know.

39:56.104 --> 39:58.898
But, I mean, "like."
What is "like"?

39:58.940 --> 40:00.942
I don't care.
I mean...

40:00.984 --> 40:03.319
Yeah.
You know what? Yeah.

40:04.988 --> 40:07.073
It's the life you got.

40:07.115 --> 40:09.743
And someday you're
gonna have to admit,

40:09.784 --> 40:11.077
you chose it.

40:11.119 --> 40:13.705
This is not just
a series of situations

40:13.747 --> 40:15.123
you keep getting
reeled into.

40:15.165 --> 40:17.167
You choose to be
out there,

40:17.208 --> 40:18.460
wherever the fuck you are,

40:18.501 --> 40:21.463
just swimming free,
cool and breezy.

40:24.299 --> 40:27.844
And I bet
people love you.

40:27.886 --> 40:32.140
And I got a lot of bile
kicking up right now, I know,

40:32.182 --> 40:35.352
but I'm not saying
they're wrong.

40:37.103 --> 40:38.396
You got a good heart.

40:39.981 --> 40:41.608
You choose to spend it
on strangers

40:41.649 --> 40:44.110
and then breeze
on down the highway.

40:44.152 --> 40:46.279
But I don't know.
Maybe that's right.

40:46.321 --> 40:47.864
You know. I mean...

40:51.284 --> 40:52.702
I bet you do some good.

40:55.163 --> 40:56.706
I bet there are a lot
of people out there

40:56.748 --> 40:58.249
who need someone
like you.

41:01.419 --> 41:02.629
But us?

41:06.007 --> 41:07.384
We're doin' just fine.

41:09.552 --> 41:10.595
(sighs)

42:00.562 --> 42:01.855
(Charlie sighs)

42:14.159 --> 42:15.326
How the fuck?

42:16.202 --> 42:17.245
What?

42:17.704 --> 42:18.997
Jesus.

42:21.207 --> 42:22.208
Augh!

42:37.098 --> 42:38.141
(sighs)

42:48.610 --> 42:50.862
(seagulls cawing)

42:57.327 --> 42:58.536
Cliff: Ah!

42:59.704 --> 43:02.999
(phone buzzing)

43:04.084 --> 43:05.085
Hello?

43:05.126 --> 43:07.128
Charlie:
Why would I kill Sterling?

43:07.170 --> 43:08.463
Where are you?

43:08.505 --> 43:09.798
You know what
he was doing?

43:09.839 --> 43:11.591
He was giving me
my life back.

43:11.633 --> 43:12.759
It makes no sense.

43:12.801 --> 43:14.678
I mean,
you can see that, right?

43:14.719 --> 43:16.596
Look, people do things.
Where are you?

43:16.638 --> 43:18.431
You heard the shots
in the dark.

43:18.473 --> 43:20.975
Did they sound like
they came from the table?

43:21.017 --> 43:22.185
I mean, Cliff, did they?

43:23.645 --> 43:25.230
No.

43:25.271 --> 43:26.398
Where are you?

43:26.439 --> 43:29.067
Look, we were set up.
You as much as me.

43:29.109 --> 43:31.236
It kills me,
but we're in this together now.

43:31.277 --> 43:33.446
You want to know
who killed the old man,

43:33.488 --> 43:34.948
we're in this together.

43:34.989 --> 43:36.074
Let me come to you.

43:36.116 --> 43:37.992
We'll figure out
what happened.

43:38.034 --> 43:39.869
Cliff, where are you?

43:40.954 --> 43:44.290
Okay, um,
I'm on a boat.

43:47.502 --> 43:48.378
You're what?

43:48.420 --> 43:50.296
State Marina? Pier 12.

43:51.589 --> 43:53.842
(phone beeping)

43:55.677 --> 43:58.138
(line ringing)

43:58.179 --> 44:00.098
Hello, Chief,
It's Cliff LeGrand.

44:00.140 --> 44:03.435
Uh, listen, I'm on my yacht,
docked down here

44:03.476 --> 44:04.769
at the end of Pier 12,

44:04.811 --> 44:08.064
and Charlie Cale is currently
on her way to me.

44:09.232 --> 44:10.150
Yeah.

44:11.234 --> 44:14.320
Yes, I can try
to keep her here. Uh-huh.

44:14.362 --> 44:15.488
You're welcome.

44:25.373 --> 44:29.210
(phone ringing)

44:30.003 --> 44:31.212
Yes, ma'am.

44:31.880 --> 44:33.173
I did. Yes.

44:35.216 --> 44:37.927
Mrs. Hasp, pleasure
doing business with you.

44:41.639 --> 44:42.932
Charlie:
Hey.

44:43.641 --> 44:44.642
Hey.

44:45.852 --> 44:47.979
That was, uh,
that was quick.

44:48.021 --> 44:50.065
Charlie:
Uh, yeah.

44:50.106 --> 44:53.068
Uh, you know,
wild coincidence.

44:53.109 --> 44:55.320
I happened
to already...

44:56.404 --> 44:58.531
Yeah, anyway, hey.

45:00.075 --> 45:01.409
Do you want
a beer?

45:02.035 --> 45:03.870
Yeah. Cool boat.

45:03.912 --> 45:05.580
The gun the police
found at the scene

45:05.622 --> 45:06.998
had your fingerprints
on it.

45:07.040 --> 45:08.291
Two shots fired.

45:08.333 --> 45:10.251
It was the gun
that shot the old man.

45:12.045 --> 45:13.546
Look, man,
all I can do

45:13.588 --> 45:14.923
is say again
what happened.

45:14.964 --> 45:16.383
I reached my hand in.

45:16.424 --> 45:18.093
I was like,
"What the hell is this?"

45:18.134 --> 45:20.387
I pulled it out,
the lights went out,

45:20.428 --> 45:21.429
and then...

45:22.639 --> 45:25.016
-Then.
-Then.

45:25.058 --> 45:27.018
Then... (scoffs)

45:27.060 --> 45:29.104
something glowed.

45:29.145 --> 45:30.897
I'd forgotten that.

45:30.939 --> 45:33.066
The chip,
the casino chip,

45:33.108 --> 45:35.777
he was, uh,
holding it.

45:35.819 --> 45:39.989
It glowed or, uh,
it started glowing like,

45:40.031 --> 45:41.866
like it turned on
or something.

45:41.908 --> 45:43.451
Does that make sense?

45:43.493 --> 45:45.912
Well, I mean, sometimes
casinos have chips that glow

45:45.954 --> 45:48.456
under black lights
for security.

45:48.498 --> 45:51.167
And with the lights out,
the shooter would have wanted
to have a target,

45:51.209 --> 45:52.585
especially if he was
trying to blend in

45:52.627 --> 45:55.880
or didn't want to get
night vision gear on or off

45:55.922 --> 45:59.050
or use a gun
with an infrared scope.

45:59.926 --> 46:01.928
Where'd he get that chip?

46:01.970 --> 46:04.264
I think it was on the table
when he sat down.

46:04.305 --> 46:06.349
He always did that
with a, with a chip.

46:06.391 --> 46:08.685
Oh shit, you're right.
He did.

46:08.727 --> 46:10.395
Yeah, I remember that.

46:10.437 --> 46:12.856
Well, gosh, anyone who knew him
would know that.

46:12.897 --> 46:15.942
I mean, Beatrix Hasp
would know that.

46:15.984 --> 46:17.652
Yes, she would.

46:19.696 --> 46:21.072
But maybe I just say
fuck it.

46:21.114 --> 46:22.657
Turn you in for it
anyway, though.

46:23.825 --> 46:25.201
(gulps)

46:25.243 --> 46:27.996
Truth and all that whatnot.
But maybe just fuck it.

46:31.124 --> 46:33.335
Yeah, I, uh...

46:34.711 --> 46:36.087
I guess I'm betting

46:36.129 --> 46:38.465
that you're even
just a little bit like me

46:38.506 --> 46:41.468
and whoever did this
for real,

46:41.509 --> 46:44.262
you want to see them
get theirs

46:44.304 --> 46:46.181
because you loved
the old man.

46:48.850 --> 46:50.310
So what do we do?

46:50.352 --> 46:52.354
Well, gee,
I don't know.

46:53.438 --> 46:54.230
We're on a boat,

46:54.272 --> 46:56.232
so I guess
for starters,

46:56.775 --> 46:58.026
we leave.

46:58.693 --> 47:01.029
(engine rumbling)

47:03.198 --> 47:04.532
What do you think?

47:05.992 --> 47:07.327
Maybe the DR.

47:08.119 --> 47:09.496
Yeah, maybe.

47:09.537 --> 47:11.581
Grab my iPad
from down below, will you?

47:11.623 --> 47:12.665
It's just down there.

47:14.376 --> 47:15.418
Alright.

47:18.630 --> 47:20.382
Okey-dokey...

47:31.976 --> 47:33.269
Alright.

48:03.258 --> 48:05.385
(boat engine stops)

48:10.807 --> 48:14.436
(sirens wailing)

48:15.770 --> 48:17.105
-(lock clicks)
-Hah.

48:17.147 --> 48:19.274
Cliff. Cliff.

48:19.315 --> 48:22.569
Hey, I found your
glow-in-the-dark things,
you son of a bitch.

48:22.610 --> 48:23.987
Cliff!
Oh, my God,

48:24.029 --> 48:26.990
I found your murder things,
your chips, you asshole.

48:27.032 --> 48:28.742
Jesus.

48:28.783 --> 48:31.536
Hey. What are the cops
going to think about that, huh?

48:31.578 --> 48:33.371
Cliff:
Put those chips
on the table

48:33.413 --> 48:35.373
against video evidence,

48:35.415 --> 48:37.208
fingerprints on the weapon.

48:37.250 --> 48:39.794
You bet a bum hand,
Charlie Cale.

48:39.836 --> 48:41.796
(laughs)
Nowhere to run.

48:43.048 --> 48:45.675
Just sit tight, Charlie.
Relax.

48:45.717 --> 48:47.594
(Cliff laughs)

48:47.635 --> 48:49.137
The fuck?

48:49.804 --> 48:51.097
Alright, man. No.

48:51.139 --> 48:53.600
Shit, shit, shit. Okay.

48:53.641 --> 48:55.018
Hey. (grunts)

48:55.060 --> 48:57.270
(panting)
Oh, fuck!

48:57.312 --> 48:58.813
Take it easy
take it easy!

49:01.983 --> 49:04.361
Ahhh!

49:07.906 --> 49:10.742
(sirens continue)

49:25.340 --> 49:26.925
Son of a bitch!

49:31.888 --> 49:34.432
Officer:
Sir, can you stay
right there for a second?

49:35.308 --> 49:37.060
Hey, she swam off.

49:37.102 --> 49:38.728
She just swam off
that way.

49:38.770 --> 49:41.064
She's got to be right off
the boat that way.

49:41.106 --> 49:42.357
-Charlie Cale.
-Cliff LeGrand,

49:42.399 --> 49:44.693
I'm FBI Special Agent
Luca Clark.

49:44.734 --> 49:47.654
Whoa. You okay?
Your eye is really fucked.

49:47.696 --> 49:49.447
No, I'm not okay,
but it doesn't matter.

49:49.489 --> 49:51.157
Charlie Cale,
the one who killed Sterling,

49:51.199 --> 49:52.409
she's getting away right there.

49:52.450 --> 49:55.245
We're not here to talk
about Mr. Sterling's case.

49:55.286 --> 49:57.288
-What?
-Can I ask you
to verify for us?

49:57.330 --> 50:00.417
Is this your voice
on this recording?

50:00.458 --> 50:01.960
Cliff:
Should we call your father?

50:02.002 --> 50:04.337
Sterling Jr.:
No, we're not calling
my fucking father.

50:04.379 --> 50:05.463
I'm handling this.

50:05.505 --> 50:07.507
Hey, you want me
to turn it up for you.

50:07.549 --> 50:08.883
Sterling Jr.:
I can handle it.

50:10.343 --> 50:11.803
Cliff:
Then tell me what to do.

50:15.765 --> 50:17.350
Cliff LeGrand,
you're under arrest

50:17.392 --> 50:19.644
for the murders of
Jerry and Natalie Hill.

50:23.690 --> 50:24.899
Inevitable.

50:29.946 --> 50:32.991
* *

51:04.022 --> 51:05.065
Thanks.

51:05.106 --> 51:06.566
(chuckles)
No.

51:09.027 --> 51:11.738
Thanks, you.
Thank you.

51:11.780 --> 51:14.074
This is the second massive case
I've closed in six months,

51:14.115 --> 51:15.116
all thanks to you.

51:15.158 --> 51:16.159
Ah.

51:16.201 --> 51:18.286
I'm just happy
you got him.

51:19.287 --> 51:21.414
Him, yeah, but no.

51:21.456 --> 51:24.501
Cliff turned like
a bad penny on Beatrix Hasp.

51:24.542 --> 51:26.628
Sold her down the river
for Sterling Sr.'s death.

51:26.670 --> 51:28.672
That's...

51:28.713 --> 51:30.382
Why do you think I'm not
arresting you right now?

51:30.423 --> 51:31.841
'Cause we're friends.

51:31.883 --> 51:33.677
(chuckles)

51:33.718 --> 51:36.429
I mean, we haven't
caught her yet,

51:36.471 --> 51:37.764
but the word
is out on the street.

51:37.806 --> 51:39.391
She's under siege
from the Southwest Syndicate,

51:39.432 --> 51:40.642
big news for us.

51:41.226 --> 51:42.727
Anyway.

51:42.769 --> 51:44.020
Well, look...

51:45.313 --> 51:46.481
I'm going to ask you
one more time,

51:46.523 --> 51:47.857
as a friend this time.

51:49.984 --> 51:51.403
You want a job?

51:53.279 --> 51:54.280
Had to ask.

51:54.322 --> 51:55.949
-Alright.
-(Charlie chuckles)

51:55.990 --> 51:57.450
Luca:
But keep my number.

51:57.492 --> 51:59.244
I stick with you,
at this rate,

51:59.285 --> 52:00.787
I'll be head of the bureau
in a year.

52:00.829 --> 52:02.330
(chuckles)

52:02.997 --> 52:05.041
So what's next?

52:05.083 --> 52:07.043
Well... what are you, a cop?

52:10.171 --> 52:11.506
Take it easy, man.

52:14.009 --> 52:15.260
There you go, hon.

52:15.301 --> 52:16.845
Come back again, okay?

52:19.431 --> 52:21.224
(doorbell dings)

52:21.266 --> 52:22.809
(can pops)

52:22.851 --> 52:26.021
(phone buzzing)

52:29.190 --> 52:30.525
Yeah.

52:30.567 --> 52:32.485
Beatrix Hasp: (over phone)
Charlie Cale.

52:32.527 --> 52:34.571
Do you know
who this is?

52:34.612 --> 52:38.658
Yeah.
Uh, I have an assumption.

52:44.789 --> 52:46.583
I mean,
Beatrix Hasp, right?

52:47.417 --> 52:48.960
Beatrix:
Yeah.

52:49.002 --> 52:50.378
Yeah, that's what I assumed.

52:51.296 --> 52:53.048
Beatrix:
Well, listen, Charlie,

52:53.089 --> 52:55.050
I'm here
with the Five Families.

52:56.801 --> 52:58.511
You're there with
all five of them?

52:58.553 --> 53:00.513
Beatrix:
Yeah, I got you on speaker.

53:00.555 --> 53:04.267
And what we are dealing
with now is a war.

53:04.309 --> 53:07.020
It's expensive
and a pain in the ass.

53:07.062 --> 53:09.105
And it is no good.
It's bad.

53:09.147 --> 53:11.358
It's ruinous,
is the word.

